{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"cummy-monkeyish-dassie","description":"## Context\n\nAn assessment of rebar's config surface (see `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` and this\nproject's `rebar.toml`) found several keys that are settled rollout flags, retired\nalternatives, or safe-to-hardcode defaults. This epic prunes the ones that are no\nlonger earning their keep, activates authenticated-authorship for this project, and\nruns a doc-accuracy sweep so the config docs match reality after the pruning.\n\nEach removal was backed by a code-level backward-compatibility investigation\n(recorded per-child). Two keys were deliberately assessed and are KEPT (below), so\nthis epic does not touch them.\n\n## Decisions (assessed, KEEP — do not remove)\n\n- **`compact.emit_legacy_signature_mirror` — KEEP.** Removal is a one-way door.\n  The key already defaults to never-emit (so runtime is unchanged), but it is the\n  documented ROLLBACK lever (`= true` + recompact) for a still-live pre-attestations\n  clone. It can break an external project on older rebar that reads a mirror-less\n  snapshot whose signature was compacted below the horizon. Retire only once the\n  readiness gate (docs/migrations.md \"Legacy signature-mirror retirement\") holds for\n  every environment sharing a store — not now.\n- **`verify.completion_floor_active` (+ `completion_priority_floor`,\n  `completion_preserve_criteria`) — KEEP DORMANT.** Fail-safe (default off ⇒ inert,\n  never drops a finding) and nearly complete; blocked only on the calibration\n  gold-set (story 77cf). Retiring throws away a near-finished noise reducer. Leave\n  as-is until 77cf decides enable-or-drop.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- The reconciler baseline rollout flags and the three settled verify defaults are\n  gone from the schema, their behavior hardcoded, and no dead back-out code remains.\n- `verify.require_signature_for_close` and the close-gate code reachable ONLY via it\n  are removed, with the shared HMAC signing/attestation machinery fully preserved.\n- Authenticated-authorship is enabled for THIS project without breaking agent writes\n  or retroactively failing historical unsigned events; the schema default stays OFF.\n- Every doc, CLI help string, and release note referencing a removed key is corrected\n  or deleted; the config docs are accurate end-to-end.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All child stories are closed.\n- [ ] `rebar` runs clean against this project's `rebar.toml` with no `unknown key … ignored` warnings (removed keys also removed from `rebar.toml`).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass on the landed result.\n- [ ] A doc-accuracy pass confirms no committed doc/help/release-note references a removed config key.","id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Prune settled/stale config values + authenticated-identity enablement + doc-accuracy sweep"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783967847211890001,"uuid":"480ef180-fcf0-4a85-bcc0-34127ad3f262"}